I simply did more damage over time, in a group, not riding anywhere near the aggro line, just using spaced rain+draughts to layer damage without aggro.<br>
<br>
Currently at 62, with my 'pathetic' spell selection, I can't actually reliably dump mana fast enough to go OOM without getting my head torn off. Crossing the aggro line by more than a little bit in PoP is a death sentence, and if I start nuking a little later, my ISoS/draught of ro combos, or ISOS+rain will do about as good as I'm going to get without getting me summoned. Throwing an extra draught in (which could get me summoned) costs me the time for the NEXT nuke because I have to concussion it off. Keeping things spaced loses me some fraction of a draught's damage (I didn't cast the extra, but no time lost on excessive concussions, so more damage through the entire fight with less chance of a wet red stain where I used to be standing).<br>
<br>
It's also fight dependant. But I think the people who think we have to be constantly on the edge of summoned and beaten either have very large manapools, very narrow 'vision', better than average spells (say, EER and/or GSS at 60, AT-&gt;SoS for 63-65), or a combination of them all. Joe wizard with etherial parch spells or less, primarily using draughts, is going to be playing a different game than the folks wielding aggro magnet big ticket spells, from what I see.<br>
